This paper is about improving accuracy in recommender systems by incorporating heterogeneous attributes and capturing sequential dependencies in both items and attributes. This topic falls under the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. The paper also uses machine learning techniques such as recurrent neural networks, which are commonly used in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with natural language processing and text analysis, which are part of the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. The paper also involves artificial intelligence techniques for recommendation systems, which are part of the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with data analysis and modeling, which are part of the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
